  "Peter Murdoch was a book with no ending and all she wanted to do with the rest of her life was to trace her finger down every page.",
  "",
  "They reached the sky, or the part of the sky where ended this world.",
  "A rectangular sheet of metal lay horizontal above them—the bottom side of a cellar door.",
  "Light seeped through along its edges.",
